question: I 100% agree with you that this an important show to have on Disney Channel, but at the same time I fell like they're close to hitting the limit of what the network will allow them to do. I think that by the end of season 3 the show will already have kicked down a lot of doors on Disney Channel, and with that goal achieved Terri, the cast and crew could move on to another network knowing they did good and succeded in their mission, and tell different storylines. If they want to, that is.
answer: Yep. I really hope this opens the door to other shows with LGBT+ rep, mental health, disabilities, and other important topics.

summary: Y’all the other day I had a dream that Cyrus and TJ were at the swings with a younger kid who was supposed to be TJ’s brother...
body: Y’all the other day I had a dream that Cyrus and TJ were at the swings with a younger kid who was supposed to be TJ’s brother and the kid was complaining about his arm being dirty. TJ then says, “you gotta stop sleeping on rocks” and the kid is like, “I wasn’t! It’s because I slept next to the fire place you set up!” And TJ responded, “oh yeah I do that. Set fires. Cuz my clothes are so fire” and Cyrus looked so confused then TJ was like, “kidding!” Then deadpans into the camera and says, “it’s because I vape” and then I woke up because that comment made me start coughing from laughter in my sleep.
